  "text": "In a study done by senol, et al. [CITATION_1] , the sensitivity, specificity, positive predictive value, and the negative predictive value of the Pathozyme TB complex plus were found to be 25%, 90%, 66.7%, and 60%, respectively. This low level of sensitivity and negative predict value low could be explained by the involved study group who were children. The data from the literature indicate that none of the available serodiagnostic tests for TB have an adequate sensitivity and specificity under various clinical conditions to be useful for diagnosing TB in children. ",
